{"type":"text","timestamp":1775870711636,"sessionID":"ses_285dbc5e8ffeKh4YmhZezcaKfm","part":{"id":"prt_d7a246dea001NlKwKH7djvR03W","messageID":"msg_d7a24472c0017JMllDd8Ix0zNN","sessionID":"ses_285dbc5e8ffeKh4YmhZezcaKfm","type":"text","text":"I'll create a proposal.md for the DockerService encapsulation in the agentcube project.","time":{"start":1775870711633,"end":1775870711633}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870711678,"sessionID":"ses_285dbc5e8ffeKh4YmhZezcaKfm","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2497530017sKCDmKZXvaCJR","messageID":"msg_d7a24472c0017JMllDd8Ix0zNN","sessionID":"ses_285dbc5e8ffeKh4YmhZezcaKfm","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-f44f9a77abd94235924d8f0ad825ff32","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Proposal: DockerService Encapsulation\n\n**AR:** AR-024  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n## Overview\n\nThis proposal outlines the design and implementation of `DockerService` within the AgentCube CLI toolkit. The service provides a Pythonic wrapper around Docker SDK operations for building, pushing, and managing container images.\n\n## Context\n\nThe `DockerService` is a core service module (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`) that encapsulates Docker SDK functionality required by the CLI's `pack`, `build`, and `publish` commands. It abstracts low-level Docker operations into a clean, testable interface.\n\n## Proposed Interface\n\n```python\nclass DockerService:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None\n    def check_docker_available(self) -> bool\n    def build_image(\n        self,\n        dockerfile_path: Path,\n        context_path: Path,\n        image_name: str,\n        tag: str = \"latest\",\n        build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]\n    def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]\n    def push_image(\n        self,\n        image_name: str,\n        registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        username: Optional[str] = None,\n        password: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]\n    def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool\n```\n\n## Key Responsibilities\n\n1. **Docker Availability Check**: Verify Docker daemon is running and accessible\n2. **Image Building**: Build images from Dockerfiles with optional build arguments (proxy support)\n3. **Image Information**: Retrieve image details (ID, size, creation time)\n4. **Image Pushing**: Authenticate and push images to registries with proper tagging\n5. **Image Cleanup**: Remove images with graceful error handling\n\n## Design Considerations\n\n- **Error Handling**: Wrap Docker SDK exceptions with descriptive error messages\n- **Logging**: Respect `verbose` flag for detailed operation logging\n- **Streaming**: Stream build/push logs to CLI for real-time feedback\n- **Tag Management**: Support retagging for registry push operations\n- **Authentication**: Handle registry login via SDK before push operations\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `docker>=6.0.0` (Docker SDK for Python)\n- Existing `rich>=13.0.0` for progress feedback\n- Standard library `pathlib`, `logging`, `typing`\n\n## Integration Points\n\n- **BuildRuntime**: Uses `build_image()` for local builds\n- **PublishRuntime**: Uses `push_image()` and `get_image_info()` for publishing\n- **PackRuntime**: No direct integration (generates Dockerfile but doesn't build)\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- All Docker operations succeed with proper error propagation\n- Verbose logging provides useful debugging information\n- Registry authentication works with standard Docker registries\n- Build/push streaming provides real-time user feedback","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775870711671,"end":1775870711676}}}}
