{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870717238,"sessionID":"ses_285dbc5e8ffeKh4YmhZezcaKfm","part":{"id":"prt_d7a24ad0f001lU2Ht54kqN3BMA","messageID":"msg_d7a2497b2001p27ScM4gYqNKU5","sessionID":"ses_285dbc5e8ffeKh4YmhZezcaKfm","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-3dcaf712e56e4047b707641f5323c417","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: This proposal describes the implementation of the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`). These commands enable users to:\n6: \n7: 1. **`invoke`**: Send payloads to deployed agents via HTTP invocation endpoints, with support for custom headers and session management\n8: 2. **`status`**: Query and display the current status of deployed agents in a formatted table\n9: \n10: These commands complete the CLI's agent lifecycle management capabilities alongside the existing `pack`, `build`, and `publish` commands.\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: ### Invoke Command\n15: \n16: The `invoke` command will provide:\n17: \n18: - **Payload submission**: POST JSON payloads to agent invocation endpoints\n19: - **Provider support**: Target both AgentCube CR (`agentcube`) and standard Kubernetes (`k8s`) deployments\n20: - **Custom headers**: Support for HTTP header customization via `--header` option\n21: - **Session management**: Automatic handling of `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header for AgentRuntime deployments\n22: - **Error handling**: Validation for payload format and header syntax\n23: \n24: **Command signature**:\n25: ```python\n26: def invoke(\n27:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\"),\n28:     payload: str = typer.Option(\"{}\", \"--payload\"),\n29:     header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(None, \"--header\"),\n30:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\"),\n31:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\"),\n32: ) -> None\n33: ```\n34: \n35: ### Status Command\n36: \n37: The `status` command will provide:\n38: \n39: - **Status query**: Retrieve deployment status from Kubernetes or AgentCube provider\n40: - **Rich formatting**: Display status information in a formatted table\n41: - **Provider support**: Query both AgentRuntime CR and standard Kubernetes resources\n42: - **Exit codes**: Exit with code 1 for `not_published` or error states\n43: \n44: **Command signature**:\n45: ```python\n46: def status(\n47:     workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\"),\n48:     provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\"),\n49:     verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\"),\n50: ) -> None\n51: ```\n52: \n53: ### Implementation Components\n54: \n55: #### InvokeRuntime Class (`agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`)\n56: \n57: - `__init__(verbose, provider)`: Initialize runtime with provider configuration\n58: - `invoke(workspace_path, payload, headers)`: Main invocation entry point\n59: - `_validate_invoke_prerequisites(workspace_path)`: Validate agent is published and metadata exists\n60: - `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube(...)`: Invoke via AgentRuntime CR with session management\n61: - `_direct_http_invocation(...)`: Direct HTTP invocation for non-AgentCube providers\n62: \n63: #### StatusRuntime Class (`agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`)\n64: \n65: - `__init__(verbose, provider)`: Initialize runtime with provider configuration\n66: - `get_status(workspace_path, provider)`: Retrieve agent status\n67: - `_get_k8s_status(metadata)`: Query standard Kubernetes Deployment/Service status\n68: - `_get_cr_k8s_status(metadata)`: Query AgentRuntime CR status\n69: \n70: ### CLI Integration\n71: \n72: Both commands will be integrated into the Typer app in `agentcube/cli/main.py`:\n73: \n74: ```python\n75: @app.command()\n76: def invoke(...) -> None:\n77:     ...\n78: \n79: @app.command()\n80: def status(...) -> None:\n81:     ...\n82: ```\n83: \n84: ## Impact Analysis\n85: \n86: ### Positive Impacts\n87: \n88: 1. **Completes CLI lifecycle**: Users can now fully manage agents from development to execution\n89: 2. **Testing workflow**: Enables end-to-end testing of deployed agents\n90: 3. **Production monitoring**: Facilitates operational monitoring via status queries\n91: 4. **Flexibility**: Support for multiple providers accommodates diverse deployment scenarios\n92: \n93: ### Breaking Changes\n94: \n95: None. These are new commands that do not modify existing functionality.\n96: \n97: ### Dependencies\n98: \n99: The implementation requires:\n100: \n101: - **Existing CLI dependencies**: `typer`, `pydantic`, `pyyaml`, `httpx`, `rich` (already in pyproject.toml)\n102: - **Kubernetes integration**: Optional `kubernetes>=28.0.0` for K8s provider support\n103: - **AgentCube provider**: Relies on client-go generated types (group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`)\n104: \n105: ### File Modifications\n106: \n107: 1. **New files**:\n108:    - `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n109:    - `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n110: \n111: 2. **Modified files**:\n112:    - `agentcube/cli/main.py`: Add invoke and status command implementations\n113:    - `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py`: Export new runtime classes\n114:    - `agentcube/__init__.py`: Update exports (potentially include `StatusRuntime`)\n115: \n116: ### Risk Assessment\n117: \n118: | Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n119: |------|------------|------------|\n120: | UnboundLocalError in InvokeRuntime | High | Ensure response is always assigned before return in `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` |\n121: | Header parsing errors | Medium | Strict validation with clear error messages |\n122: | Provider authentication issues | Medium | Leverage existing `AgentCubeProvider` and `KubernetesProvider` auth handling |\n123: | Status display inconsistencies | Low | Use Rich Table for consistent formatting |\n124: \n125: ## Alternatives Considered\n126: \n127: ### Alternative 1: Single combined command\n128: \n129: **Approach**: Combine invoke and status into a single `agent` command with subcommands (e.g., `agent invoke`, `agent status`)\n130: \n131: **Rejected because**:\n132: - Adds unnecessary nesting for two independent commands\n133: - Less discoverable than flat command structure\n134: - Inconsistent with existing `pack`, `build`, `publish` flat structure\n135: \n136: ### Alternative 2: External HTTP client integration\n137: \n138: **Approach**: Rely entirely on external tools (curl, wget) for invocation and kubectl for status\n139: \n140: **Rejected because**:\n141: - Loses integration with CLI workspace context\n142: - Requires manual metadata management\n143: - No session header handling for AgentRuntime CR\n144: - Inconsistent user experience across commands\n145: \n146: ### Alternative 3: Provider-specific commands\n147: \n148: **Approach**: Create separate commands per provider (e.g., `invoke-agentcube`, `invoke-k8s`)\n149: \n150: **Rejected because**:\n151: - Command explosion as providers grow\n152: - Duplicates validation and error handling logic\n153: - Provider selection via flag is more consistent with `publish` command\n154: \n155: ## Acceptance Criteria\n156: \n157: ### Invoke Command\n158: \n159: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube invoke --payload '{\"key\": \"value\"}'` successfully POSTs to agent endpoint\n160: - [ ] `--header` option accepts multiple headers in `key:value` format\n161: - [ ] Invalid JSON payload exits with code 1 and prints error message\n162: - [ ] Invalid header format exits with code 1 and prints expected format\n163: - [ ] Session ID header is automatically added for AgentRuntime deployments\n164: - [ ] Not-published agent exits with guidance to publish first\n165: - [ ] Verbose mode logs detailed HTTP request/response information\n166: \n167: ### Status Command\n168: \n169: - [ ] Displays agent status in formatted Rich table with key fields\n170: - [ ] Exits with code 1 for `not_published` status\n171: - [ ] Exits with code 1 for error status\n172: - [ ] Successfully queries AgentRuntime CR status when provider is `agentcube`\n173: - [ ] Successfully queries K8s Deployment/Service status when provider is `k8s`\n174: - [ ] Verbose mode logs detailed status retrieval steps\n175: \n176: ### Integration Tests\n177: \n178: - [ ] End-to-end test: pack → build → publish → invoke → status\n179: - [ ] Test invoke with both providers (`agentcube` and `k8s`)\n180: - [ ] Test status with both providers\n181: - [ ] Test error handling for unpublished agents\n182: - [ ] Test header parsing and transmission\n183: \n184: ## Implementation Timeline\n185: \n186: Estimated effort: **5-7 days**\n187: \n188: | Phase | Duration | Deliverables |\n189: |-------|----------|--------------|\n190: | Phase 1: Runtime implementation | 2 days | `InvokeRuntime` and `StatusRuntime` classes |\n191: | Phase 2: CLI integration | 1 day | Typer command implementations in `main.py` |\n192: | Phase 3: Error handling and validation | 1 day | Payload/header validation, error messages |\n193: | Phase 4: Testing | 1-2 days | Unit tests, integration tests |\n194: | Phase 5: Documentation | 0.5 days | Command help text, examples |\n195: \n196: ## References\n197: \n198: - CLI Toolkit Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n199: - CLI Specification: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` (Requirements 487-519 for invoke, 509-519 for status)\n200: - AgentRuntime CR API: `deployment/client-go.md`\n201: - Python SDK (for reference HTTP patterns): `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n(End of file - total 201 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal describes the implementation of the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`). These commands enable users to:\n\n1. **`invoke`**: Send payloads to deployed agents via HTTP invocation endpoints, with support for custom headers and session management\n2. **`status`**: Query and display the current status of deployed agents in a formatted table\n\nThese commands complete the CLI's agent lifecycle management capabilities alongside the existing `pack`, `build`, and `publish` commands.\n\n## Scope\n\n### Invoke Command\n\nThe `invoke` command will provide:\n\n- **Payload submission**: POST JSON payloads to agent invocation endpoints\n- **Provider support**: Target both AgentCube CR (`agentcube`) and standard Kubernetes (`k8s`) deployments\n- **Custom headers**: Support for HTTP header customization via `--header` option","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775870717226,"end":1775870717235}}}}
