{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775870718915,"sessionID":"ses_285dbc5e8ffeKh4YmhZezcaKfm","part":{"id":"prt_d7a24b3c20016HFK2gP1Ogq7MK","messageID":"msg_d7a24ad6d001wqyqbK3g035F2D","sessionID":"ses_285dbc5e8ffeKh4YmhZezcaKfm","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870748287,"sessionID":"ses_285dbc5e8ffeKh4YmhZezcaKfm","part":{"id":"prt_d7a25263e001yiy0q7shLyJwgk","messageID":"msg_d7a24ad6d001wqyqbK3g035F2D","sessionID":"ses_285dbc5e8ffeKh4YmhZezcaKfm","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-19ba67e429814df2a50a1ec22262a81b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal describes the design and implementation of `DockerService` as a core service module within the AgentCube CLI toolkit. The service provides a Pythonic abstraction layer over Docker SDK operations required by the CLI's `pack`, `build`, and `publish` workflows.\n\n## Scope\n\n### DockerService Class (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`)\n\nThe `DockerService` class will encapsulate all Docker SDK interactions:\n\n- **Docker availability check**: Verify Docker daemon is running and accessible\n- **Image building**: Build container images from Dockerfiles with optional build arguments\n- **Image information retrieval**: Query image metadata (ID, size, creation time)\n- **Image pushing**: Authenticate and push images to container registries\n- **Image removal**: Clean up local images with graceful error handling\n\n**Class interface**:\n```python\nclass DockerService:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None\n    def check_docker_available(self) -> bool\n    def build_image(\n        self,\n        dockerfile_path: Path,\n        context_path: Path,\n        image_name: str,\n        tag: str = \"latest\",\n        build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]\n    def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]\n    def push_image(\n        self,\n        image_name: str,\n        registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        username: Optional[str] = None,\n        password: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, str]\n    def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool\n```\n\n### Method Responsibilities\n\n#### `check_docker_available()`\n- Attempts to connect to Docker daemon via `docker.from_env()`\n- Returns `True` if connection succeeds, `False` otherwise\n- Logs warnings when Docker is unavailable (respecting `verbose` flag)\n\n#### `build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag, build_args)`\n- Builds image using `client.images.build()`\n- Streams build logs to CLI for real-time user feedback\n- Supports build arguments for proxy configuration\n- Tags image as `{image_name}:{tag}`\n- Returns dict with `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n- Raises `RuntimeError` on build failure\n\n#### `get_image_info(image_name)`\n- Retrieves image metadata via `client.images.get()`\n- Returns dict with `id`, `repo_tags`, `size`, `created`\n- Uses internal `_format_size()` for human-readable size formatting\n- Raises `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` if image doesn't exist\n\n#### `push_image(image_name, registry_url, username, password)`\n- Logs in to registry if credentials provided via `_docker_login_sdk()`\n- Retags image if `registry_url` is specified via `_tag_image_sdk()`\n- Streams push logs to CLI\n- Returns dict with `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n- Handles authentication errors gracefully\n\n#### `remove_image(image_name)`\n- Removes image via `client.images.remove()`\n- Returns `True` on success\n- Logs warning and returns `False` on failure\n- Forces removal if image has dependent containers\n\n## Design Considerations\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n- Wrap Docker SDK exceptions with descriptive error messages\n- Maintain stack traces in verbose mode for debugging\n- Use `RuntimeError` for unrecoverable failures (Docker unavailable, build failures)\n- Log warnings for non-critical issues (image removal failures)\n\n### Logging and Verbosity\n- Respect `verbose` flag for detailed operation logging\n- Use Python standard `logging` module\n- Log at INFO level for normal operations, DEBUG for verbose mode\n- Integration with CLI's verbose flag passed from runtime classes\n\n### Streaming Output\n- Stream build and push logs to CLI using generators\n- Provide real-time feedback to users during long-running operations\n- Decode Docker API log lines for display\n\n### Registry Authentication\n- Support standard Docker registry authentication\n- Handle both Docker Hub and private registries\n- Store credentials securely via Docker SDK (not in code)\n- Support `registry_url` parameter for non-Docker-Hub registries\n\n## Integration Points\n\n### BuildRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`)\n- Uses `build_image()` for local Docker builds\n- Uses `get_image_info()` after build to retrieve image metadata\n- Uses `remove_image()` for cleanup on build failure\n\n### PublishRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)\n- Uses `push_image()` for publishing to registries\n- Uses `get_image_info()` for image metadata display\n- Passes registry credentials from metadata to push operation\n\n### CLI Commands\n- Indirect usage via runtime classes (no direct CLI integration)\n- Errors propagated through runtime error handling\n- Verbose flag passed from CLI commands through runtimes\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Positive Impacts\n\n1. **Separation of concerns**: Docker operations isolated from business logic\n2. **Testability**: Easy to mock Docker SDK for unit testing\n3. **Maintainability**: Single source of truth for Docker operations\n4. **Reusability**: Consistent Docker behavior across CLI commands\n5. **Error handling**: Centralized, consistent error messages\n\n### Breaking Changes\n\nNone. This is a new service module that doesn't modify existing functionality.\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- **New dependency**: `docker>=6.0.0` (Docker SDK for Python)\n- **Existing dependencies**: `pathlib`, `logging`, `typing`, `rich` (for logging integration)\n\n### File Modifications\n\n1. **New file**:\n   - `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`: Complete `DockerService` implementation\n\n2. **Modified files**:\n   - `agentcube/services/__init__.py`: Add service docstring\n   - `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`: Use `DockerService` instead of direct SDK calls\n   - `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`: Use `DockerService` for push operations\n\n3. **Configuration**:\n   - `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`: Add `docker>=6.0.0` to project dependencies\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|------------|\n| Docker SDK API changes | Low | Pin version to `docker>=6.0.0,<7.0.0` |\n| Registry authentication failures | Medium | Comprehensive error messages, retry logic |\n| Build log streaming issues | Low | Test with various Dockerfile scenarios |\n| Proxy build_args handling | Medium | Validate build_args format before use |\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Direct Docker CLI integration\n\n**Approach**: Use `subprocess` to call `docker build`, `docker push`, etc.\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Requires parsing CLI output instead of structured data\n- Less portable across operating systems\n- No native Python error handling\n- Harder to test\n\n### Alternative 2: No abstraction layer\n\n**Approach**: Directly import and use Docker SDK in runtime classes\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Duplicates Docker initialization logic\n- Inconsistent error handling across runtimes\n- Harder to mock for testing\n- Mixes concerns (Docker operations vs agent lifecycle)\n\n### Alternative 3: Third-party Docker wrapper\n\n**Approach**: Use existing Docker wrapper libraries\n\n**Rejected because**:\n- Adds unnecessary dependency\n- Existing libraries may not match CLI requirements\n- Custom implementation allows tighter integration with CLI features\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n### Core Functionality\n\n- [ ] `check_docker_available()` returns `True` when Docker daemon is running\n- [ ] `check_docker_available()` returns `False` when Docker daemon is stopped\n- [ ] `build_image()` successfully builds images from Dockerfiles\n- [ ] `build_image()` streams build logs to console\n- [ ] `build_image()` supports build_args for proxy configuration\n- [ ] `get_image_info()` returns correct image metadata\n- [ ] `get_image_info()` formats size in human-readable format\n- [ ] `push_image()` successfully pushes to Docker Hub with credentials\n- [ ] `push_image()` handles registry URL retagging\n- [ ] `remove_image()` removes images successfully\n- [ ] `remove_image()` returns `False` on failure and logs warning\n\n### Error Handling\n\n- [ ] Raises `RuntimeError` when Docker is unavailable\n- [ ] Raises appropriate exceptions for build failures\n- [ ] Handles authentication failures gracefully\n- [ ] Logs detailed errors in verbose mode\n- [ ] Provides user-friendly error messages\n\n### Integration\n\n- [ ] BuildRuntime successfully uses DockerService for local builds\n- [ ] PublishRuntime successfully uses DockerService for publishing\n- [ ] Verbose flag is respected for logging\n- [ ] Errors propagate correctly through runtime classes\n\n### Testing\n\n- [ ] Unit tests for all public methods\n- [ ] Mock Docker SDK for testing without Docker daemon\n- [ ] Integration tests with real Docker daemon\n- [ ] Test proxy configuration via build_args\n- [ ] Test registry authentication and push\n\n## Implementation Timeline\n\nEstimated effort: **3-4 days**\n\n| Phase | Duration | Deliverables |\n|-------|----------|--------------|\n| Phase 1: Core implementation | 1.5 days | `DockerService` class with all methods |\n| Phase 2: Error handling and logging | 0.5 day | Comprehensive error handling, verbose logging |\n| Phase 3: Runtime integration | 0.5 day | Update BuildRuntime and PublishRuntime |\n| Phase 4: Testing | 1 day | Unit tests, integration tests |\n| Phase 5: Documentation | 0.5 day | Docstrings, examples, pyproject.toml update |\n\n## References\n\n- CLI Toolkit Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md` (lines 216-243)\n- CLI Specification: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` (Requirements 547-563 for Docker integration)\n- Docker SDK Documentation: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n- BuildRuntime: `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`\n- PublishRuntime: `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775870748237,"end":1775870748285}}}}
